1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 g6 {Going for ... g6 here is questionable, for sure. We are getting some sort of Grünfeld, but an amazing version for White.} 5. Bxc4 Bg7 6. O-O O-O 7. Nc3 {Please note that with a pawn on c6 , this would have been a Schlechter Slav! But without it, Black's position is very dubious. Black can try many moves, but nothing is even close to equality. The best move could be c5 , but this is covered in the Schlechter Slav , while others are just bad.} Ne8 {Black reroutes his knight to d6 , but I am not sure what it really gives him.} (7... Bg4 8. h3 Bxf3 9. Qxf3 {just gives White the bishop pair.}) 8. h3 Nd6 9. Bb3 b5 ({Or} 9... Nc6 10. e4 {.}) 10. e4 b4 11. Nd5 {Stockfish evaluates +2! The c7 -pawn is a target. Next, moves such as Bf4 and Rc1 will exert enormous pressure on Black.} *

