rickiest seems to be Kh1 , as it is the least expected and contains a devious idea.} 24. Kh1 (24. Kf1 Be3 25. Qxe4+ Bxe4 26. Rxe3 f5 27. Ra1 {, with the idea a3 , is very logical as well. Black still needs to be a bit careful.}) 24... Be3 25. Qxe4+ Bxe4 26. Rxe3 f5 27. Rc1 {The point. White wants to win the a6 -pawn, of course, and there is no good way to prevent it... as there is a hidden stunning idea of Bd3 !} Rd2 ({Winning a pawn on e4 .} 27... a5 28. Bd3 {is similar.}) ({Or} 27... Ke7 28. Bxa6 Rd2 29. Bb7 {and again White grabs a pawn on e4 .}) 28. Bd3 {Black has to neutralize the Rc8 threat and we grab a pawn on e4 .} *

