is very challenging for Black. White launches a direct aggression on the kingside, which may not be so easy to react to, especially if caught off guard. So far, there was one game, Mamedyarov-MVL (2023) but still, this line is completely unexplored.} Rc8 {The best option for Black is to trade a pair of rooks to reduce White's attacking potential.} 15. Rxc8+ {I think White should trade rooks right away to worsen the position of the queen.} Qxc8 16. g5 {Putting more pressure on Black, and some choice or room to go wrong.} Bxf3 (16... Nd5 {without the bishop trade is risky for Black.} 17. h4 Nd7 18. Ne4 {with pressure. Next, we'll push the h -pawn.}) 17. Qxf3 {The most logical recapture.} Nfd7 {This is quite similar to the mainline.} 18. h4 Rc7 19. Ne4 {With pressure on the kingside.} *

