1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 e6 5. Bxc4 c5 6. O-O a6 7. Re1 {An interesting line that I tried in the 2023 US Champs against Jeffery Xiong and managed to obtain a very promising position. There are several ideas associated with this move. White prepares e4 , anticipates ... cxd4 followed by exd4 , and then Re1 would be perfectly placed on e1 , and finally, the bishop has a safe square on f1 if needed.} ({I am not going into too much detail on this line as it is an alternative to} 7. b3 {, our main move but still, I want to offer more ideas and possibilities to the repertoire to be less predictable.}) 7... Nbd7 {was tried in some games, but it is simply bad here. The idea of ... Nbd7 is common in the QGA, but not here. Someone may confuse the lines, though, and it could give us a chance to quickly get an advantage.} 8. e4 b5 9. Bd5 {And Black is in trouble. We can see how useful Re1 can be!} ({exd5? exd5+ Be7 d6+- Nxd5 exd5 Be7 dxe6 fxe6} 9. Qe2 {Nf6 dxc5 Bxc5 Bg5⩲}) *

