1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 e6 5. Bxc4 c5 6. O-O a6 7. Re1 {An interesting line that I tried in the 2023 US Champs against Jeffery Xiong and managed to obtain a very promising position. There are several ideas associated with this move. White prepares e4 , anticipates ... cxd4 followed by exd4 , and then Re1 would be perfectly placed on e1 , and finally, the bishop has a safe square on f1 if needed.} ({I am not going into too much detail on this line as it is an alternative to} 7. b3 {, our main move but still, I want to offer more ideas and possibilities to the repertoire to be less predictable.}) 7... Nc6 {The main move in Benjamin Gledura's Chessable course. I think that, objectively, it is the best.} 8. Nc3 Be7 {This move was played by Jeffery Xiong. It is a very solid option.} 9. dxc5 Qxd1 10. Rxd1 Bxc5 {In this endgame, White has a slight edge, but eventually, Black should be able to hold. There are two ideas that White can try.} 11. Nd2 ({I decided to keep this as a main move. It is a bit different than} 11. Bd2 {(offered as alternative ) but also less explored. The knight is headed to b3 , from where it can exert some pressure on the queenside.}) 11... O-O 12. Nb3 Ba7 (12... Be7 13. Be2 {looks playable, too, with similar ideas: Bd2 , Rc1 , Na4 .}) 13. Be2 Bd7 14. Bd2 Rac8 15. Bf3 {With a playable endgame. White will play Ne4 soon and try to play Rac1 - Nc5 in the future.} *

