1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 e6 5. Bxc4 c5 6. O-O a6 7. Re1 {An interesting line that I tried in the 2023 US Champs against Jeffery Xiong and managed to obtain a very promising position. There are several ideas associated with this move. White prepares e4 , anticipates ... cxd4 followed by exd4 , and then Re1 would be perfectly placed on e1 , and finally, the bishop has a safe square on f1 if needed.} ({I am not going into too much detail on this line as it is an alternative to} 7. b3 {, our main move but still, I want to offer more ideas and possibilities to the repertoire to be less predictable.}) 7... Nc6 {The main move in Benjamin Gledura's Chessable course. I think that, objectively, it is the best.} 8. Nc3 Be7 {This move was played by Jeffery Xiong. It is a very solid option.} 9. dxc5 Qxd1 10. Rxd1 Bxc5 {In this endgame, White has a slight edge, but eventually, Black should be able to hold. There are two ideas that White can try.} 11. Bd2 ({This is what I tried against Jeffery and got a promising position as he confused lines. But as the solution is already well known, I decided to keep it only as an alternative to my main recommendation} 11. Nd2 {.}) 11... O-O 12. Rac1 Bd7 13. Be2 {White completed development and has some pressure in the center. There are ideas of Na4 or even Nd5 !?. For this reason, it makes sense to move the bishop... which is a mistake.} Rfd8 {Unfortunately, this move should equalize. There are no tactics that exploit undefended Bc5 . Here, Ng5 is also not great as Black can bring the bishop to e7 from where it guards d6 square.} 14. Na4 (14. Nd5 Ne4 $1 {is just fine for Black.}) 14... Ba7 15. Be1 {This keeps the game a bit more alive. The idea is Nc5 on the next move.} ({After} 15. Nc5 Bxc5 16. Rxc5 Ne4 {, Black takes away the bishop pair and White has nothing.} 17. Rcc1 Nxd2 18. Rxd2 Be8 {and a draw is nearly inevitable.}) 15... Nd4 {Black needs to play this move.} 16. Nxd4 Bxa4 17. b3 Bd7 18. Nf3 {And the position is roughly equal, but with Ne5 - Bf3 next, White may have a bit easier game.} *

