1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c6 4. e4 Bb4 5. cxd5 exd5 (5... cxd5 $2 6. e5 {is a terrible French for Black.}) 6. e5 {White seizes space and comfortably controls the center. With a3 next, White will either get the pair of bishops or force the bishop to find a place for himself... which may not be easy because I can't think of any square where this bishop would be well placed. Therefore, we will likely get the pair of bishops.} Ne7 {Black can also either delay ... c5 or play without it altogether.} 7. Nf3 O-O {Playing without ... c5 is unlikely to be good for Black:} 8. Bd3 Bf5 9. O-O Nd7 10. Ne2 {Thanks to the strong center White has clear advantage.} *

