jectively it should not yield an advantage after} Nf6 $1 13. c5 Ne8 $1 {Black manages to put just enough pressure on the Bd6 to successfully deal with it and pretty much equalize.}) 12... Qf4 ({And if} 12... Bxf3 $4 13. Bxe4 Bxd1 14. Bf5+ $1 {and Black is forced to self-pin with} Rd7 {.}) 13. Bxe5 Qxe5 14. Nxe5 Bxd1 15. Bf5+ ({An important intermezzo, intending to take on f7 . After the immediate} 15. Nxf7 $6 Bg4 $1 16. h3 Be6 17. Nxd8 Kxd8 {, Black is not worse here.}) (15. Raxd1 Nh6 {is just equal.}) 15... Kc7 16. Nxf7 {The best try.} Bh5 {This was played in Aronian-Vallejo, 2010.} 17. Nxd8 Kxd8 18. f3 ({Aronian chose} 18. g4 {, which is also interesting, but the engine claims this to be stronger. The rooks come to d1 and e1 and White is much better in the resulting endgame.}) *

