 the pawn.} Qc6 14. a3 {Restricting the knight and preparing Bd3 .} Nc7 15. Bd3 e5 {This seems like a decent try to restrict activity of White's pieces but we are just ready to strike in the center.} 16. Bxe5 {The thematic blow.} fxe5 17. Nxe5 Nxe5 18. Qh5+ Kd8 19. Rxe5 ({With a very strong attack. Maybe engines are able to avoid immediate loss here with Black, but on a human level, defending such positions is a daunting task. Bd7 Rd1 Kc8 Re7!? Qf6 Rxd7 Kxd7} 19. Bf5 Ke7 {Rd7+ Kf8 Rxc7 Re8} 20. g3 {or} Bxf5 $5 {Bxf5} 21. Qxf5 {Kb8 Rxc5} Qf6 22. Qd7+ {Rc8 Rd6 Qf8 b4± are two sample continuations.}) *

