side with b4 - b5 , or play more positionally with c5 .}) 10. Bf3 {A very interesting rare line that poses a lot of practical problems to Black. The first one is right there - where should Black retreat with the queen?} Qg5 {The queen is the most active here and it supports ... e5 . In some lines, Black has an idea of ... Qa5 +.} 11. Ne2 Nh6 12. Ng3 e5 {This is another option for Black, but combined with ... Nh6 , it is a worse version.} 13. b4 {Since the c6 -square is not as well supported as with ... Ne7 , this is a strong move.} Nf5 14. b5 Nb8 15. Ne4 Qd8 16. O-O {This is definitely unpleasant for Black.} *

