side with b4 - b5 , or play more positionally with c5 .}) 10. Bf3 {A very interesting rare line that poses a lot of practical problems to Black. The first one is right there - where should Black retreat with the queen?} Qg5 {The queen is the most active here and it supports ... e5 . In some lines, Black has an idea of ... Qa5 +.} 11. Ne2 Nh6 12. Ng3 e5 {This is another option for Black, but combined with ... Nh6 , it is a worse version.} 13. b4 {Since the c6 -square is not as well supported as with ... Ne7 , this is a strong move.} Nf5 14. b5 Nd4 15. Ne4 Qf5 16. Bg2 cxb5 17. O-O {Black is under pressure. With only moves, he manages to avoid defeat, but White is still better:} Qg6 (17... bxc4 $2 18. Ba3 {exploiting the d6 -square.}) 18. Bxe5 Bh3 19. Nd6+ Kf8 20. Bg3 Bxg2 21. Kxg2 Ne6 {Here, White has some choice.} 22. Kh1 {I would recommend this move with ideas of Qd5 and f4 . From a practical point of view, it is still easy to go wrong here with Black, so I think White should have good chances.} bxc4 23. f4 {The f-pawn heads to f6 to attack the black castle.} Qd3 24. f5 Qxd1 25. Raxd1 Nec5 26. f6 {Black is under pressure. There is only one move that keeps the balance.} Rg8 {But White still has good chances here:} 27. fxg7+ Rxg7 28. Rd4 ({To be honest, I am not sure why not immediately} 28. Be5 {, but from what I understand, White should improve the rook first as Be5 does not run away, and the engine claims Black has no good defense from it. In general, White has a strong initiative here.}) ({Rd8} 28. Be5 Rg6 29. Rxf7+ Kg8 {Rf1} 30. Rd7 {Nf5 Kf7 Nh4+ Ke6 Nxg6 hxg6 Rxd7} Nxd7 31. Bc3 Nac5 {Kg2⩲ is a sample line.}) *

