nk it poses certain problems for Black. So far, the b7 -pawn needs attention.} Be6 {It seems like this is the most obvious move here - but this is precisely what White wants, as the bishop is not well placed on e6 .} 14. Qc2 {Now Black needs to decide what to do with the Ne5 .} Bg4 {This may seem logical but it runs into trouble.} 15. Ng5 {With big advantage for White.} Rad8 (15... Bxe2 $4 16. Nd5) 16. Bxg4 Nexg4 17. h3 Ne5 18. Bd2 {With a healthy extra pawn.} *

