1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c5 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Nf3 Nf6 6. Bg5 ({An alternative approach involves playing} 6. g3 {, which is also challenging. In this course, I focus on .}) 6... Be6 {This is a recent trend in the Tarrasch Defense. Black supports the center.} 7. e3 ({I would recommend this positional approach.} 7. Bxf6 Qxf6 8. e4 $5 {is an interesting alternative that can cause Black problems as well. Initially, I had planned on recommending this...but I encountered some obstacles, and my final conclusion was that Black should be fine with correct defense. Still - it is quite challenging, and Black needs to know his lines. At the end of the day, e3 is much simpler and has more playability. There is no way for Black to force a draw with this choice!}) 7... c4 ({Having supported the center, Black goes for a standard idea of gaining space on the queenside. Black wants to play ...Bb4 , which resembles the Ragozin. I would argue, though, that White has some advantage here in two ways.} 7... Nc6 $6 8. Bb5 {is good for White.}) 8. Be2 Bb4 ({Black can begin with} 8... Nbd7 9. O-O Bb4 {, move order. It avoids the e4 ideas, but it does not change much.}) 9. O-O {White has two main ideas here: 1) the e4 breakthrough, or 2)  Ne5 with some pressure in the center or an attack on the kingside with f4 , etc.} Nc6 {This is not a good square for the knight. The knight is not supporting its colleague on f6 , and White can immediately exploit it:} 10. e4 Be7 ({•} 10... dxe4 11. Nxe4 Be7 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. Rc1 {is also bad for Black.}) ({•} 10... Bxc3 11. bxc3 dxe4 {seems a logical human choice, but in reality it is a bad one. After} 12. Nd2 $1 {White recovers the pawn on the next move with a big advantage.}) 11. Bxf6 Bxf6 12. Rc1 {Surprisingly, Black is going to lose a pawn!} O-O (12... dxe4 13. Nxe4 Bxd4 {is logical, but after} 14. Bxc4 $1 {Black is in trouble because the king is still in the center. The main line should be} Bxb2 15. Nd6+ Kf8 16. Rb1 Bxc4 17. Nxc4 {where White will soon take b7 and even with the queens off the board, Black will be in big trouble because of the weak king and uncoordinated pieces - especially the rooks.}) 13. exd5 Bxd5 14. Nxd5 Qxd5 15. Bxc4 {And Black will suffer for the rest of the game...} *

