k establishes a good defense against Bxa4 .) Qc6 Rab1} a6 {. Here, White has an excellent positional exchange sacrifice:} 20. Rxa4 $1 bxa4 21. Qxa4 {with some pressure. The key is that Black cannot control the b-file and White's bishop pair is very strong.}) ({Reb8} 19. Bg3 $1 {And there is no Rb6 .}) *

