ize on it.} 11. f4 ({Passing on the opportunity of Bxf6 for now and going for the direct attack on the kingside! I find it the most challenging from a human point of view, but in case you are not in the mood for such sharp play,} 11. Bxf6 {is calmer, and I cover it as an alternative as well.}) 11... Bxc3 {Sooner or later, Black needs to eliminate the Nc3 before occupying the e4 -square.} 12. f5 {But we are not recapturing the bishop! Black has the first of many chances to go wrong.} Bxb2 {This already loses, as Black's kingside collapses.} 13. fxe6 Bxa1 {This capture must also be addressed, but in reality it only speeds up Black's defeat.} 14. exf7+ Rxf7 (14... Kh8 15. Rxf6 $3 {Wins as well, of course.}) 15. Nxf7 Nbd7 (15... Kxf7 16. Bxf6 gxf6 17. Qb1 $3 {With a crushing double attack on b7 and h7}) 16. Bg4 {With a totally winning attack.} *

