ize on it.} 11. f4 ({Passing on the opportunity of Bxf6 for now and going for the direct attack on the kingside! I find it the most challenging from a human point of view, but in case you are not in the mood for such sharp play,} 11. Bxf6 {is calmer, and I cover it as an alternative as well.}) 11... Bxc3 {Sooner or later, Black needs to eliminate the Nc3 before occupying the e4 -square.} 12. f5 {But we are not recapturing the bishop! Black has the first of many chances to go wrong.} Bd7 {Inaccurate.} 13. bxc3 Ne4 (13... Qxc3 $2 {This is a wrong option because it allows White to take f6 (at the right time) and destroy the king's defense.} 14. Rc1 $1 Qa3 15. Bxf6 $1 Qxe3+ ({Or} 15... gxf6 16. Ng4 Qd6 17. Qe1 {is overwhelming.}) 16. Kh1 gxf6 17. Bg4 Qg5 18. Rc3 $1 {With Rg3 following and a crushing attack.}) 14. Be7 Re8 15. Bb4 Qc7 16. Bf3 {With Bxe4 to follow. Black is in a difficult situation, and he should probably sacrifice an exchange with Rxe5 , but this is never equal.} Nf6 17. g4 {After this, White's attack gains in strength and momentum!} *

