 Rae1 {White prepares a potential e4 -break, but he keeps the other rook on f1 for potential ideas of f4 if Black should castle kingside.} O-O 15. Qc2 {A useful retreat, shifting attention to the kingside and creating a 'silent threat'...} Nd7 ({Black must prevent Ne5 . For example,} 15... c6 $2 16. Ne5 {with the idea f4 is suddenly very strong! That's why we moved Qc2 - Black does not have the Bxe5 and ... d4 resource.}) 16. e4 ({It is logical to strike in the center now, as everything is ready.} 16. Na4 $5 {can be played too.}) 16... dxe4 17. Bxe4 c6 ({We would answer} 17... g4 {in the same way, with the strong} 18. d5 $1) 18. d5 {A well-timed strike in the center before Black can successfully install a knight on d5 , with an annoying blockade.} cxd5 19. Bxd5 {With the advanced kingside pawns, Black will always have issues with his weakened kingside. In this position here in front us, and in similar situations.} *

