e f6 -knight wanders away the center.} a5 15. a3 Rfe8 16. Rac1 Rac8 {Some standard moves by both sides. Finally, it is time for Na4 or Ne2 .} 17. Na4 (17. Ne2 $5 {rerouting the knight to f4 is also playable.}) 17... Ne4 {This was played in Giri-Carlsen, 2020.} 18. Bxe4 dxe4 19. Nd2 ({The e4 -pawn needs attention, while White has a nice game on the queenside.} 19. Qxe4 $4 Bb3) 19... f5 20. Nc4 ({An improvement over Giri's} 20. Nc5 {.}) 20... Qc7 (20... Bxc4 21. Qxc4+ {is, of course, clearly better for White.}) 21. Nc5 Nxc5 22. dxc5 Bxc4 23. Qxc4+ Kg7 24. Red1 Rcd8 25. Rd4 {It is White who controls the d -file, and Black has a long way ahead to try to hold.} *

