 is required here, but White should win:} Qa1+ 21. Qb1 Qc3+ 22. Kd1 Rfd8 23. Rd2 Rab8 24. Qc1 Rxd2+ 25. Bxd2 Qd3 26. Rh3 {The key move. White manages to consolidate and win:} Qf1+ 27. Kc2 Qc4+ 28. Bc3 Qxa2+ 29. Bb2 Qa4+ 30. Kb1 Qe4+ 31. Ka1 {And the rook comes in handy on the 3rd rank with a winning position.} *

