1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bf4 c6 6. e3 Bf5 {By far, the most popular move in this position. The idea is to quickly develop the bishop, before White plays Bd3 and stops Black from doing so. If Black does not play this move, he may face issues with the Bc8 in the long run.} ({Still, there are some alternatives:} 6... Bd6 {has been covered earlier and for Nf6} 7. Bd3 {, see the 5... Nf6  lines .}) 7. Nge2 Nd7 {The main move here. Generally, Black delays ... Nf6 to keep the h4 -square under control.} 8. h4 {An interesting try to seize space on the kingside, despite the e7 -bishop looking at the h4 -square. There are potential issues with the Bf5 as it will run under Ng3 . The idea of h4 is to prevent Black from playing ... Bg6 and force the bishop to e6 . Then, Bd3 can be played, followed by Nf5 . Additionally, the h4 -pawn can be used to play h5 and weaken Black's kingside.} Ngf6 {The main move here. Black completes the development, ignoring White's expansive ambitions on the kingside.} 9. Ng3 {Chasing the bishop away. Please note that the bishop cannot go to g6 now (as it would normally want), which definitely is good news for White.} Be6 (9... Bg4 $6 {only helps White as the pawn on f3 is useful in many similar positions.} 10. f3 Be6 11. Bd3) 10. Bd3 {White creates an idea of Nf5 , trying to get the pair of bishops.} Nb6 {Black is getting ready for the Nf5 idea with the intention of trading on f5 , followed by ... Bd6 , trading the dark-squared bishops. It is worth noting that this idea only works before Black castles. After Black castles, White obtains the idea of meeting ... Bd6 with Bg5 , as we'll see.} 11. Qc2 ({White should not rush:11.} 11. Nf5 Bxf5 12. Bxf5 Bd6 {is fine for Black, as} 13. Bg5 h6 {is just equal.}) 11... O-O 12. Nf5 {Consequent and objectively the right move here.} Bxf5 13. Bxf5 Bd6 {As announced, this is not good anymore.} 14. Bg5 {And ... h6 can be simply ignored for now:} h6 15. O-O-O Re8 (15... hxg5 $2 16. hxg5 Nfd7 $4 17. Bh7+ Kh8 18. Bg8+ $1 Kxg8 19. Qh7#) 16. Bxf6 {It is time to trade as White will use the weakened kingside to launch some initiative or attack:} Qxf6 17. g4 g6 18. Bd3 Kg7 19. Kb1 {With good play on the kingside.} *

