Nf3 {cxd4 cxd4} Bb4+ {, as with the inclusion of Rb1 we put pressure on the queenside and the knight is not ideal on c6 either, as very often it belongs to d7 .}) 9... Bb4+ 10. Bd2 Bxd2+ 11. Qxd2 O-O 12. Bb5 {An active move that prevents ... b6 for now.} Bd7 {This is not a good square for the bishop. It belongs to b7 normally.} 13. O-O Ne7 (13... a6 {is even worse:} 14. Bd3 b5 15. d5 $1 {and White crushes through in the center.}) 14. Bd3 ({Play may continue} 14. Bc6 {h4} h6 15. Rfe1 {and White is clearly better thanks to our pawn center. In the future, White may play even via g4 - g5 !?}) *

