Qc7 , but the inclusion of a4 -... a6 seems to help White as we are able to restrict ... b5 , unlike earlier.} 11. Be2 {The best square for the bishop. Again, with Bd3 we run under ... Nc6 -... Nb4 ideas, while Bb3 with a4 is probably a bit worse.} b6 (11... cxd4 12. cxd4 {does not change much.}) 12. O-O cxd4 (12... Bb7 $2 13. d5) 13. cxd4 Bb7 14. Bd3 {Supporting the center. This looks very nice for White.} Nd7 {This is too passive.} 15. Qe2 {Keeping an eye on the a6 -pawn and preventing ... Rac8 .} *

