Qc7 , but the inclusion of a4 -... a6 seems to help White as we are able to restrict ... b5 , unlike earlier.} 11. Be2 {The best square for the bishop. Again, with Bd3 we run under ... Nc6 -... Nb4 ideas, while Bb3 with a4 is probably a bit worse.} b6 (11... cxd4 12. cxd4 {does not change much.}) 12. O-O cxd4 (12... Bb7 $2 13. d5) 13. cxd4 Bb7 14. Bd3 {Supporting the center. This looks very nice for White.} Nc6 {Black needs to put pressure on White's center and try ... Nb4 .} 15. Rb3 {This was played by Ding Liren against Wesley So and I like it a lot. White has ideas of lifting the rook to the kingside or the center.} Na5 {Black probably needs to kick the rook away from the 3rd rank.} 16. Rb2 {Intending a future Rd2 . In Ding-So, 2019, followed:} Nc6 17. Rd2 Rfd8 18. Bb2 {And White is better thanks to our strong center.} *

