1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bg5 Be7 6. e3 c6 7. Bd3 Nbd7 {In this move order, I discuss plans where Black does not castle kingside.} 8. Nge2 Ne4 {This standard idea is quite dubious in this position.} 9. Bxe7 Nxc3 (9... Qxe7 $2 {loses a pawn:} 10. Bxe4 dxe4 11. Ng3 Nf6 12. Qc2 {and Black cannot defend the e4 -pawn.}) 10. bxc3 Qxe7 11. O-O {White is clearly better. We can play via e4 or c4 .} *

