1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bg5 Be7 6. e3 O-O 7. Bd3 Nbd7 {One of the plans here is to play without ... c6 . Let's see how it works out.} 8. Nge2 Re8 9. O-O Nf8 {White has many possibilities. I like the most the minority attack now.} 10. b4 {Taking advantage that Black cannot take on b4 due to Bxf6 . Our idea is of course b5 , as Black sooner or later will need to play ... c6 which will create a weak c6 -pawn.} a6 11. a4 {Renewing the idea.} Ne6 {Black probably needs to grab the b4 -pawn anyway, but it is a worse version than before.} (11... Be6 12. b5 {is better for White.}) 12. Bh4 g5 13. Bg3 Bxb4 {Here, instead of Rb1 , it is even stronger to play} 14. Be5 c6 15. a5 {With a blockade of the queenside, and keeping ideas of crushing on the kingside.} *

