1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bg5 Be7 6. e3 O-O 7. Bd3 Nbd7 {One of the plans here is to play without ... c6 . Let's see how it works out.} 8. Nge2 Re8 9. O-O Nf8 {White has many possibilities. I like the most the minority attack now.} 10. b4 {Taking advantage that Black cannot take on b4 due to Bxf6 . Our idea is of course b5 , as Black sooner or later will need to play ... c6 which will create a weak c6 -pawn.} Ne6 {Here, we should not trade on f6 , but play 11. Bh4 ! instead, which involves a pawn sacrifice.} 11. Bh4 g5 12. Bg3 Bxb4 13. Rb1 {We lost a pawn but Black weakened his kingside with ... g5 . It is totally worth it for us! We can play Be5 , Ng3 , maybe f4 (or just f3 - e4 ) with strong initiative in all scenarios.} *

