1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bg5 Be7 6. e3 O-O 7. Bd3 c6 {The most popular move here, but Black can try so many move orders that I tried to simplify what we are doing as White: our plan is Bd3 , Nge2 and O-O on nearly anything and there would be some transpositions.} ({Black can begin with} 7... h6 8. Bh4 {but we should anyway transpose as we play Nge2 on nearly anything.}) ({Beginning with} 7... Re8 8. Nge2 {should also transpose as Black needs ... c6 sooner or later.}) 8. Nge2 h6 {Recently, the main theory advocates for including this move. It is debatable whether it helps Black or not, but one thing for sure - now Black cannot play with ... g6 and White's bishop has faster path towards the f2 -square ( f3 - Bf2 ).} (8... Nbd7 {can be played too but after} 9. O-O {we transpose after either} h6 {or Re8 . And if Nh5 then Bxe7 Qxe7} 10. Qd2 {with the plan of f3 - e4 ; I analyzed similar positions in the section where Black delays castling.}) 9. Bh4 {Here, Black has a huge choice.} Ne8 {This idea is quite fashionable recently. Black brings the knight to d6 where it is well-placed to face a minority attack. I think that both Bg3 and Bxe7 offer some edge to White.} 10. Bg3 Nd6 11. O-O Re8 12. Qc2 Bf8 {The main position in this line. Now we have to choose our plan. Engines are not much help here, as there are countless suggested moves with more or less equal evaluations. For this reason, I tried to look for some logical human ideas. Unfortunately, it is not so easy to play f3 - e4 , but I think the minority pawn attack is the simplest approach.} 13. b4 {This was tried recently in Vitiugov-Gledura (2023) and I think it offers good practical chances.} Nd7 14. b5 {This is generally good news. But things are not entirely easy, as Black may try to occupy the c4 -square.} Nb6 {Here, things are not entirely trivial, as shown in Demuth's and Schandorff's courses. However, I think White can put Black under pressure after my recommendation.} 15. a4 {Keeping the tension and potentially preparing a5 - a6 !} Nbc4 {Black should jump in right away. But now White has an interesting idea:} 16. Bxd6 {And apparently, Black does not have 'easy' recapture as everything has certain drawbacks.} Nxd6 {This seems very natural, preventing Bxc4 .} 17. a5 {But after this, with the idea of a6 , the pressure on the queenside gives White a great version of the minority attack.} *

