1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bg5 Be7 6. e3 O-O 7. Bd3 c6 {The most popular move here, but Black can try so many move orders that I tried to simplify what we are doing as White: our plan is Bd3 , Nge2 and O-O on nearly anything and there would be some transpositions.} ({Black can begin with} 7... h6 8. Bh4 {but we should anyway transpose as we play Nge2 on nearly anything.}) ({Beginning with} 7... Re8 8. Nge2 {should also transpose as Black needs ... c6 sooner or later.}) 8. Nge2 h6 {Recently, the main theory advocates for including this move. It is debatable whether it helps Black or not, but one thing for sure - now Black cannot play with ... g6 and White's bishop has faster path towards the f2 -square ( f3 - Bf2 ).} (8... Nbd7 {can be played too but after} 9. O-O {we transpose after either} h6 {or Re8 . And if Nh5 then Bxe7 Qxe7} 10. Qd2 {with the plan of f3 - e4 ; I analyzed similar positions in the section where Black delays castling.}) 9. Bh4 {Here Black has a huge choice.} Re8 (9... Nbd7 {can be played too but again after} 10. O-O {there should be a transposition.}) 10. O-O Nbd7 {The inclusion of ... h6 and Bh4 does not change much, and I would recommend stopping ... b5 right away.} 11. a4 {This is not the most obvious move here, as it weakens the b4 -square and normally White should go for minority attack on the queenside, not a “weird” a4 . However, the idea is somewhat deep. The point is that Black actually wants to play ... b5 , ... a5 , etc (as shown here after 10...a5 ) and with 11.a4 we are stopping it. And in case of ... a5 , Black’s knight is not getting to b4 , and the b4 -square in that case is not relevant.} a5 {This the most human move - after all, the b4 -square is now under Black's control. But we don't care as we play via f3 - e4 and now also Black can forget about queenside play with ... b5 , as in the main line.} 12. f3 Nf8 13. Kh1 (13. Qc2 $5 {is possible too, as in Bok-Kramnik (2022).} Ne6 14. Rad1 b6 15. h3 Bb7 16. Bf2 Rc8 17. e4 c5) 13... Ne6 14. Rc1 b6 15. Bf2 {White is clearly better.} *

