the idea of e4 . As Black does not have ... Nc4 (as after 13... Nb6 ), we can play more actively, even though 14. Ng3 is playable too.} Bd6 ({Black needs to stop e4 .} 14... Qb8 15. Nce2 c5 16. Bf5 {looks uncomfortable for Black due to pressure on the d5 and d7 squares.}) 15. Qd2 Qb8 16. Bg3 {Supporting the Nf4 and slowly preparing e4 , or the more positional Nce2 , followed by maneuvering the knight to d3 .} *

