erything seems to be ready for the attack.} 17. Bxd6 Rxd6 18. Ng3 Bxd3 (18... Bg6 19. Qc2 {is just the same as ... Bxd3 needs to be played anyway.}) 19. Qxd3 {The position is double edged but I like White's chances more. The ideas of e4 and Nf5 should make White's position easier to play.} Qg6 (19... Ne7 20. e4) 20. e4 dxe4 21. Qb5 ({White definitely has strong initiative. With very precise (and awkward) moves Black holds but OTB good luck finding all that... Nd8} 21. Nf5 Re6 22. d5 Re5 23. Ne3 {with continued pressure.}) *

