 learning process, I decided to keep only 8. Nc3 . 8. Qc2 objectively does not offer that much anyway, but if you are interested to explore it, I encourage you to do so!}) 8. Bd3 {This helps White to achieve e4 .} a6 ({Preparing ... c5 . Black can start with} 8... Bb7 9. e4 a6 {which transposes as White anyway plays} 10. a4 {to prevent ... c5 .}) 9. a4 {Preventing ... c5 !} Bb7 10. e4 {To prevent ... c5 anyway.} b4 {Played with the idea of ... c5 next - but again, we have the Nbd2 - Nc4 plan at our disposal.} 11. e5 Nd5 12. Nbd2 c5 13. Nc4 cxd4 14. Bg5 ({Black does not have Be7 due to} 14. Nd6+ {. White’s lead in development is nearly decisive...}) *

