 to different positions. Let's take a look.} ({Please note that} 7. b3 $2 {is a serious error due to} e5 $1 {and Black begins to take over.}) 7... O-O 8. e4 dxe4 9. Nxe4 Nxe4 10. Bxe4 {This position has been very popular years ago, but modern engines simply don't see equality here. White's space advantage is substantial.} Nf6 {This move is by far the most popular and, in truth, not all that exceptional. It only helps White to drop the bishop back to c2 , and Bg5 would now come as a pin.} 11. Bc2 c5 {Black needs to do something in the center, but it is already a bit late for that.} 12. Qd3 {A strong move, lining up towards the h7 -pawn. Bg5 is a threat! Black does not have many good moves now.} b5 ({Probably the best move already - but here White simply is up a pawn.} 12... h6 13. Ne5 $1 cxd4 14. Bf4) (12... cxd4 13. Bg5 Re8 14. Nxd4 ({g6} 14. Qxd4 Be7 15. Qh4)) 13. cxb5 (13. b3 $5 {Funnily enough, the engine likes this move even more. But there is nothing wrong with grabbing a free pawn!}) 13... Bb7 14. dxc5 Bxc5 15. Bf4 {With an extra pawn and a big advantage.} *

