 to different positions. Let's take a look.} ({Please note that} 7. b3 $2 {is a serious error due to} e5 $1 {and Black begins to take over.}) 7... O-O 8. e4 dxe4 9. Nxe4 Nxe4 10. Bxe4 {This position has been very popular years ago, but modern engines simply don't see equality here. White's space advantage is substantial.} Qc7 11. Bc2 {The usual retreat, intending Qd3 .} b6 (11... c5 {transposes here .}) 12. Qd3 {Provoking the weakening of the kingside.} f5 ({Not a good sight for Black, but the alternative is worse.} 12... g6 $2 {weakens the kingside.} 13. Bh6 Rd8 14. Rfe1) 13. Re1 Nf6 14. Bd2 {Of course, this is great for White.} c5 15. dxc5 bxc5 16. Qe2 {After Bc3 we will keep control of e5 , putting even more pressure on the weakness on e6 .} *

