lowing a spectacular blow.} 16. Bxe6 {This position looks terrible for Black, if not for one calm move...} O-O ({Cold-blooded, but works and keeps Black in the game.} 16... fxe6 $4 17. Rxe6+ {just wins for White.}) 17. Bxd7 Qxd7 {White is up a pawn but Black has some compensation. Still, it is Black that must be very careful here.} 18. Bf4 Bxf3 {Less precise than 18... Qg4 .} 19. gxf3 Qd4 (19... Qd5 $2 20. Rac1 $1 Qxf3 21. Qc4) 20. Be5 Rxc5 21. Qxh7+ Kxh7 22. Bxd4 Rg5+ 23. Kf1 {White is clearly better in this endgame: up a pawn, with a bishop vs a knight and pawns on two sides of the board!} *

