1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 a6 5. Bd3 {I would recommend this move, trying to play without Nc3 and keep the flexibility of developing the knight to d2 .} (5. Be2 $5 {This could be another good option for White which is rarely played, but deserves attention as well.}) (5. Nc3 {is the main move of course, but the point is that after} e6 {we enter the classic Semi-Slav with ... a6 which is very well studied and objectively not necessarily better than 5. Bd3 . And 5. Bd3 is way simpler to learn! Moreover, Black can play the classical Chebanenko with 5... b5 , which only increases the lines to be learned. Therefore, I would choose 5. Bd3 !}) 5... Bg4 ({The main move here. By including a6 , Black deals with Qb3 ideas. If Black plays} 5... dxc4 {we will have sooner or later a transposition to QGA (similarly as after e6 Bd3 dxc4 ) .} 6. Bxc4 e6 7. O-O b5 {(7... c5 see QGA.)} 8. Bd3 Bb7 9. a4 Nbd7 10. e4 {see the Slav 4... e6  Meran .}) (5... b5 $6 {without Nc3 , this move is not good for Black.} 6. b3 {White supports the c4 -pawn and will develop the knight to d2 .}) 6. Nbd2 {Reinforcing the Nf3 , so that we can recapture with the knight any moment.} e6 7. O-O {I would use this move to avoid Black's ideas related to ... c5 , which surprisingly work quite well with the inclusion of h3 and ... Bh5 .} Nbd7 {The most standard move.} 8. h3 ({I think we should make Black declare the intentions of the Bg4 . The most normal retreat is Bh5 , but} 8. Bf5 {seems possible too, while} Bxf3 {gives away voluntarily the bishop pair so I don't take it serously.}) 8... Bf5 {This move is counterintuitive and it strategically looks unsound. Black voluntarily gets a bad pawn structure.} 9. Bxf5 exf5 10. cxd5 {A well timed move, as recapturing with the knight is risky, while recapturing with the pawn leads to a position with an awkward pawn structure for Black.} Nxd5 {Worse than ... cxd5 .} 11. Qc2 g6 12. e4 {White opens the center and Black's king faces certain issues.} fxe4 {The critical line.} 13. Nxe4 Be7 14. Bh6 {And Black cannot castle!} *

