n d5 which does not allow for Rxa6 .}) 13... Be7 14. Nc3 c5 {This move can be played as well, but the resulting endgame is not equal.} 15. dxc5 (15. Nb5 $5 {is also interesting.} O-O 16. dxc5 Bxc5 17. e4) 15... Bxc5 16. Nxd5 Nxd5 17. Nd3 Bb6 18. Rhc1 ({With multiple ideas: Ba5 , Rc4 , e4 . There is some pressure on the queenside and the game continues pretty much risk-free for White. O-O} 18. Ba5 Bxa5 19. Rxa5 a6 20. e4 Ne7 {Rc7 Nc6} 21. Ra4 {Rfd8 Rxb7 Nd4+ Ke3 Nc2+ Kd2 Ne1 Kxe1 Rxd3 Rxa6} Rd8) *

