ad of Qc2 is that right now we have this additional option of swinging the queen to f2 ! Generally, White wants to keep the majority of pieces on the board to make the most out of his space advantage.} f5 {A possible move. Black makes sure to seize the control over the e4 -square. However, the resulting position is pretty passive for Black.} 12. Nf3 Nf6 13. Qc2 Bg7 14. Bd3 (14. h3 O-O 15. Bd3 Ne4 16. Ne2) 14... Ne4 15. Ne2 ({Generally, White tries to provoke some weakening of Black's queenside, or prepare some breakthrough on the kingside with g4 . There is lots of maneuvering play ahead. In the clickable line you can see potential courses of action.} 15. O-O {h3} Nd7 16. a3 Ndf6 {Rg1 Be6} 17. b3 {Qe8 Bb2} Ra7 18. Ne5 {and g4 next.}) *

