1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 Bf5 5. Nc3 e6 6. Nh4 Bg6 {A very solid line for Black. Without provoking f3 (as after 6... Be4 ) this line navigates toward more positional play. White has a wide choice.} 7. Be2 Nbd7 8. O-O {I like this line for White. I have been waiting quite a while to play it, but unfortunately so far I have not been given the chance to do so. White is in no hurry with Nxg6 and completes his development first. Black's main moves are 8... Bd6 or 8... Be7 , but other moves have also been tried.} Be7 {This move was tried recently by Daniil Dubov.} 9. Bd2 {I would wait with capturing the bishop on g6 for now. Also, playing 9. g3 (see illustrative line ) slightly weakens the kingside as well (even though it may seem imperceptible), so this developmental move would be my recommendation.} O-O 10. Nxg6 {We capture the bishop now that Black has castled - since there is no more danger on the h-file.} hxg6 11. Qb3 {One of the few moments where I would recommend Qb3 over Qc2 .} Qc7 12. cxd5 {I would recommend going for this pawn structure.} exd5 {This structure is perfectly playable. White has many possible plans.} 13. Rac1 {Setting up a little trap...} Nb6 ({Here, White has many possible plans to choose from.} 13... Rfe8 $2 14. Nxd5 $1 {is what we hope for!}) (13... Rac8 14. g3 Rfe8 15. h4 {with the idea of Kg2 - Rh1 .}) 14. Kh1 {Stepping aside from g1 - a7 diagonal and slowly preparing f3 - e4 . Black can play in several ways, but generally White should have some edge. Normally, Black should meet f3 ideas with ... c5 , so we should be ready for that. I show some example lines, but of course, Black can try something else.} Qd7 15. Rcd1 {I would not rush yet with f3 . This move serves two purposes: it anticipates that Black will play ... c5 in the future and thus Rd1 will be ideal, and in case of plans ... Qe6 -... Nc4 , we can always play Bc1 .} (15. f3 $5 {is less good due to} Rac8 {and Black is in time with counterplay.}) 15... Qe6 16. Bc1 {Further prophylaxis, as ... Nc4 was an idea.} Rac8 17. f3 ({Finally, we are ready. Due to some X-rays between queens, we have some edge. For example, c5 dxc5 Bxc5} 17. e4) *

