eached in both Ding-Bu (2022) and Artemiev-Gledura (2021). It seems to me to be a worse version of the main line, since neither ... Qe7 nor ... a6 improves Black's position much over that seen in the main line.} c5 {Black should probably play this move now, but it is quite similar to the main line.} 15. a4 ({Again, I would recommend going for the position with the isolated pawn. It feels to me that it offers better chances to play for a win than the symmetric positions after} 15. dxc5 {.}) 15... cxd4 16. exd4 Nb6 (16... Rac8 17. Bf1 {does not change much.}) 17. Bf1 Nbd5 18. Qb3 {Something like this I analyze in depth in the main line.} *

