Ne2 {But this is an easy solution as grabbing the h4 -pawn is not feasible. Also, White may play g4 and win an important tempo.} dxc4 ({After} 12... Bxh4+ $2 13. Kd1 $1 {the pin is very unpleasant.}) 13. Qxc4 Nd7 14. O-O-O {With the advantage, thanks to the kingside play.} *

