ingside, since on the queenside he is safe and Black does not have much counterplay.} Qb8 16. g3 {Now g4 was not great as there was no Ba5 tempo with queen on b8 .} g5 17. Bd3 Qb7 18. Bc3 {And White is better because of the bishop pair and a clear plan, while Black is generally struggling with active ideas.} *

