ock to the kingside with ... g5 but neither offers full safety.} g5 {An attempt to lock the kingside. Now, we should keep the h6 idea for the right moment and not rush with it.} 18. Na4 Qb7 {Or anywhere else.} 19. Bc3 {With an unpleasant position for Black. The king is chronically weak and h6 is always going to be a threat.} *

