 tries to guard the d5 -pawn.} 18. Bf3 Nb6 {Black created a threat of ... b4 , therefore White needs to play a very important move that must be memorized.} 19. e4 {Opening the center up. Black is not in time to generate his initiative.} d4 20. f5 gxf5 21. exf5 Qc8 22. Ne2 {Again, Black's pawn mass is stopped by White’s pieces and g4 - g5 is coming.} *

