moving the rook from the diagonal, in anticipation of Bf3 .} 18. Bf3 {We play this move anyway.} O-O 19. g4 d4 20. Ne2 {This is quite similar to the main line, with the difference that now White may consider grabbing the d4 -pawn as there is no ... Rc8 hitting our queen.} d3 ({Probably the best move, looking for counterplay, as we will see in a moment.} 20... dxe3 $2 21. g5 Nh5 22. Bxe3) 21. Rxd3 c4 22. Rdd1 Nc5 {Black controls the d3 -square here, but his king is weak, which is a more serious issue.} 23. g5 Rxd1 24. Rxd1 Nfd7 25. h4 Nd3 26. Nc3 ({With the attack. Qe6} 26. Rh1 Nxc1 27. h5 $1 {and} Nd3 $2 {loses after} 28. hxg6 {, so Black's only option is Nb6□ hxg6} fxg6 29. Rc1 Bxg5 (29... Qxe3 $2 {Nd5+-})) *

