1. d4 d5 2. c4 Nf6 {This opening is often played by novice chess players who do not understand the concept of controlling the center. The d5 -pawn is not sufficiently supported now (as it is after 2... c6 or 2... e6 ), and White can play cxd5 and e4 , since Black cannot recapture the pawn. However, there are some hidden rocks that White needs to watch out for.} 3. cxd5 c6 {This pawn sacrifice does not work but it can have the effect of confusing people.} 4. dxc6 {White needs to grab the pawn - otherwise Black will recapture ... cxd5 and we will get an Exchange Slav.} Nxc6 5. Nf3 e5 {The best try to create some chaos.} 6. dxe5 Qxd1+ 7. Kxd1 Ng4 8. Ke1 ({Black has some activity that somewhat compensates for the pawn, but it is very speculative. Bc5} 8. e3 Ngxe5 9. Nxe5 Nxe5 10. Bd2) *

