1. d4 d5 2. c4 Nc6 {The Chigorin Defense is not much played nowadays at the highest level, but it does happen from time to time. In the 2000s it was taken up by Morozevich and later by Rapport, and both achieved good results, but in general it is a rather suspect opening for Black.} 3. Nf3 Nf6 {Obviously a bad move.} 4. cxd5 Qxd5 5. Nc3 {White will comfortably seize control over the center.} Qa5 6. Bd2 ({The only thing we need to know is that after ... Qa5 , this move is the strongest, renewing the idea of e4 . It resembles the Scandinavian Defense, but in a horrible version for Black - the engine evaluates this as +2.5! Bg4} 6. e4 {Bxf3 gxf3} Nxd4 {Nd5+- or Qb6 d5} 7. Nxd4 e5 {Nd7} 8. Be3 {Nxe5} Qa4 {c6 O-O-O+-}) *

