th an advantage.}) ({•} 10... a6 11. a4 {does not really change much.}) 11. b5 {Now Black has only one move that holds Black's position.} Qc7 {Everything else is much worse. Now, there is some tension on the c-file.} 12. Bd2 {Supporting the c-file and now the idea is Rfc1 . I think White is better.} Nxc3 {The most forcing line.} 13. Bxc3 cxb5 {We might try 14. cxb5 , but it is only marginally better for White, or go for maximum with cxd5 !} 14. cxd5 exd5 15. Nh4 {White takes advantage of weakened long diagonal and weak pawn d5 and f5 .} ({The line continues with Nf6! (only move) Nxf5 Bxf5} 15. Qxf5 Qxc3 {Bxd5+! Kh8 Bxa8 Rxa8} 16. e3 {with unbalanced material; however, White should be better as Black's minor pieces do not have outposts and White's central pawns may quickly move forward.}) *

