Black attempts to play ... e5 , but as mentioned earlier, now it likely won't work.} (10... Bd7 11. Bb2 b5 {is another plan for Black. But now with b3 on the board, we are well-guarded on the queenside, and with Black not being able to play ... e5 , we can play more positionally.} 12. e3) 11. Ba3 {I like this move the most as Black can pretty much forget about ... e5 . If that's the case, Black can try something on the kingside or queenside, but White is everywhere better.} b5 12. e3 a5 {The queenside plan. Again, we bring our knight to f4 .} 13. Ne2 Bd7 14. Bb2 {With some edge, as Black does not have an active plan and we may try to exploit the weakening of the queenside in the future.} *

