1. d4 e6 2. c4 Bb4+ {The Keres Defense can be considered a variant of the Nimzo or Bogo Indian. Before developing the Ng8 , Black quickly brings out the bishop, perhaps intending to make ... f5 in the future. But it is still worse than the standard Nimzo, since now White is not pinned.} 3. Bd2 ({An alternative is} 3. Nd2 {which is also good, but} Bxd2+ {is the simplest to learn in my opinion. Of course, White does not play Nc3 as there are better options than transposing back to the Nimzo!}) 3... Bxd2+ {This was recently tried by Magnus Carlsen, following up with ... f5 , which is one of the main benefits of playing without ... Nf6 . Please note that White wants to play e4 and quickly control the center, so Black should do something about it. Alternatives involve 3... a5 , 3... Qe7 and 3... c5 .} 4. Qxd2 {Black must do something right now about e4 .} f5 {A logical continuation that takes advantage of the delayed development of Ng8 . The position resembles the Dutch, but with the bishops already exchanged, which helps White. For example, if Black opts for a Stonewall, the lack of the dark-squared bishop will certainly be a problem.} ({•} 4... d5 5. Nc3 Nf6 {- for this line, see here .}) ({•} 4... d6 5. Nc3 Nf6 {- see here .}) ({•} 4... b6 5. Nc3 Bb7 {This plan is also not great for Black. White gets a comfortable version of the Owen Defense.} 6. e4) 5. g3 {I think that going for the bishop's fianchetto is the best approach. White could have started with 5.Nc3 as well but sooner or later the bishop should come to g2 .} Nf6 6. Bg2 O-O 7. Nc3 d6 {Black goes for a flexible center, trying to play ... e5 .} 8. Nf3 {Black should try to prepare ... e5 here. There are two moves that attempt to do so.} Nc6 9. Rd1 {A prophylaxis against ... e5 .} Ne7 10. O-O Ng6 {There were some games with the ... Ne7 - g6 maneuver, but this plan seems pointless.} 11. Rfe1 ({White is much better. Perhaps} 11. d5 {should be played, but this results in an awkward Stonewall with Ng6 . Allowing e4 is even worse:} Bd7 12. e4 fxe4 13. Nxe4 Nxe4 {Rxe4 Qf6} 14. h4) *

