ith the Nd5 idea, either right away or after} 11. dxe5 dxe5 12. Nd5) 11. Nh4 {White prepares e4 . However, also an idea is to play f4 !} Nf7 12. f4 e5 13. e4 ({And White is more ready than Black for the action in the center. fxe4} 13. Ne4 Nxe4 14. Bxe4 {Bh3 Rfe1} g5 15. Ng2 $1) *

