 takes advantage of Black's pawn being still on c7 .} Bb7 (9... Nxd5 10. Bxd5 Rb8 {is possible but quite sad for Black.} 11. Qe2 a5 12. Be3 Bb7 13. Bxb7 Rxb7 14. Rad1) 10. Nxe7+ Qxe7 11. Bd3 {Supporting the center. Having won the bishop pair this looks better for White.} Rfe8 12. d5 {This looks good for White. We intend to play c4 and build a strong center, so Black needs to play 12... Nc5 .} Nc5 13. Bg5 {But now this move creates this unpleasant pin.} h6 14. Bh4 {It will be difficult for Black to get out of this pin, as ... g5 will be met by Nxg5 . Without the dark-squared bishop, this pin can be a big problem for Black.} *

