 possible expansion on the queenside, we should take advantage of that. Black has a couple of options, but nothing really equalizes.} Bf8 (10... exd4 11. Nxd4 Ne5 12. Bb3 {or Ba2 , followed by f4 is similar to 8... exd4 .}) 11. Be3 ({Simple development. We prepare d5 . Be careful and do not fall for} 11. d5 $6 b5 $1 12. axb6 Nxb6 {and Black gets good counterplay.}) 11... exd4 ({Black should not delay it any further.} 11... Qc7 12. d5 {already works well as our bishop keeps an eye on the b6 -square.}) 12. Bxd4 {But this position looks very good for White. Our plan, in general, should be something like b4 - b5 .} *

