he e5 -pawn:} 10. Nxe5 dxe5 11. Qxe5 $2 Ng4 $1 {and Black takes over, e.g.} 12. Qf4 Bd6 13. e5 Nxe5 14. Rxe5 Qc7) 9... Ne5 {This idea makes more sense before White plays a4 .} 10. Ba2 {Right now we don't have to go passively to f1 .} Re8 11. h3 ({Controlling the g4 -square and preparing f4 . I think Black's position is uncomfortable. For example, Bd7} 11. f4 Ng6 12. Kh1) *

