1. d4 d6 {This move order allows White to immediately take control of the center with e4 . This definitely seems the right way, although Black can play 2... Nf6 , which unfortunately does not allow us to play c4 and transpose to the Pirc or Philidor. However, I think we should not fear these openings, and I think my recommendations are quite convincing! Therefore: 2. e4 !} 2. e4 {Don't worry about having to study too many lines: my suggestions are relatively easy to learn, and we have an edge almost everywhere because of the space advantage.} ({• I would have loved to recommend here} 2. Nf3 {but unfortunately in the event of a transposition to the King's Indian after} Nf6 3. c4 g6 4. Nc3 Bg7 5. e4 O-O {we don't get the Be2 - Be3 system, which I covered in part 1, as we already have Nf3 on the board.}) ({• After} 2. c4 {Black can play} e5 $1 {and unfortunately, we cannot get our King's Indian setups with Be2 - Be3 . We never want to play d5 so early,} 3. Nc3 {is met by} exd4 {and recapturing with the queen is not ideal. So the only reasonable move here seems} 4. Nf3 {but now Black can play e4! Ng5} f5 {and this line is pretty good for Black.}) 2... Nf6 3. Nc3 {Here, Black can choose between Philidor and Pirc.} g6 {Against the Pirc, I would recommend an aggressive plan, yet still quite easy to learn.} 4. Be3 {White wants to play Qd2 , O-O-O and attack on the kingside. However, there are also ideas connected with f4 and building a strong center. Using the move order 4. Be3 avoids many lines after the immediate 4. f4 that are considered OK for Black.} c6 {Black prepares ... b5 without weakening the long diagonal. We need to play now via f4 .} 5. h3 {Although 5. f4 was possible, it makes it easy to remember: After 4... c6 or 4... a6 we play 5. h3 !} Bg7 ({• After} 5... b5 {we can just play} 6. a3 {and f4 on the next move. Black's pawn on b5 may be just weakening Black's position.}) ({•} 5... Nbd7 $6 {with idea ... e5 is not advisable now.} 6. f4 e5 7. Nf3 {White is much stronger in the center.}) 6. f4 O-O 7. Nf3 b5 8. e5 Nh5 9. Bd3 Ng3 10. Rg1 {And the Ng3 will be soon kicked out, or even trapped. White will castle queenside.} *

