re it is in fact clearly stronger.} O-O (6... Ng4 {is again pointless:} 7. Bg5 {where h3 will kick out the knight soon.}) 7. Bh6 {Trading the bishops is a good thing for White. Now, we can either play positionally with Bd3 and O-O , or more aggressively with h4 - h5 and O-O-O . Possibly, the latter is a better choice.} d5 {Probably the best move, as played by Magnus Carlsen. But it is extremely rare and also leads to a stable advantage for White.} (7... b5 8. Bd3 {is better for White, as mentioned after 6... b5 . keeping an option of castling both kingside and queenside. The trade of dark-squared bishops should offer an advantage to White.}) 8. Bxg7 Kxg7 9. e5 Ne4 10. Nxe4 dxe4 11. Ng5 Bf5 {Somewhat more solid than 11... c5 as played by Magnus.} 12. f3 {I did not find a way to win the e4 -pawn, but I think that after 12. f3 our strong center offers us an advantage anyway.} exf3 13. Nxf3 Qd5 14. Bd3 Bxd3 15. Qxd3 {Black still needs to work hard to earn equality and without a doubt, White is better.} *

